    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** standing as our undisputed anchor, boasting a dominant 81.47 efficiency score. Despite a neutral park factor, **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a high-upside matchup against Andre Pallante and a prime #2 spot in the order, positioning him as the primary engine for our HR and RBI production. We are also leaning heavily into our speed-focused lineup architecture to mitigate the scarcity of the SB category. **Hyeseong Kim** (70.53) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (65.42) are high-priority starts today; their scores are significantly buoyed by facing pitchers with slow deliveries, which historically drives their effective SB potential to elite levels, compensating for the risks of lower batting order positions.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today was keeping **Caleb Durbin** on the bench. While his 43.74 score reflects a viable utility player, the optimizer favored our active starters due to the daunting presence of Tarik Skubal on the mound. **Caleb Durbin** fell just short of the threshold, as his profile\u2014while strong in speed\u2014could not justify the risk against a sub-3.00 xERA arm when compared to the platoon advantages offered by **Colt Keith** (69.64). We are also closely monitoring the pending status of **Kazuma Okamoto** and **Victor Scott II**; while **Victor Scott II** is locked in as a sub-goal speed threat, any defensive adjustments or lineup shifts could impact his dynamic platoon edge against Lance McCullers Jr.\n\nWe must exercise caution regarding the top of our order against elite arms. Both **Kyle Schwarber** (53.83) and **Trea Turner** (55.23) are facing Chris Sale, a matchup that severely suppresses their base projections due to his elite SP skill. While **Kyle Schwarber** maintains value through his high xwOBA, both players are startable but carry a higher floor risk today. We remain cautious with **Junior Caminero** as well, whose score of 55.03 reflects the extreme difficulty of facing Paul Skenes. We will continue to hold **Christian Yelich** and **Zac Veen** in inactive slots while waiting for health and roster updates to restore their eligibility.",
